<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
<tr><td></td><td align="center"><h3>Divine Sanction Charter</h3></td></tr>
 <tr>
     <td width="15">&nbsp;</td>
	<td>


&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;      This guild is dedicated to
helping its members learn and grow in many directions. Raids and Events
within our Legions structure promote teamwork. Our Officer program promotes
leadership abilities while our Code of Conduct promotes self 
responsibility.
All of these skills will be invaluable to our members in EverQuest.
<br>
<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;       Divine Sanction is not limited in race, class or level in our membership;
we believe that everyone has qualities that can add to the guild experience
as a whole. We do screen our new members carefully to ensure that their
goals and personalities fit well with the guild's. We are a close-knit 
guild
consisting of an ever expanding circle of friends and EverQuest family.
<br>
<br>

 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;      Through effective leadership and supportive members we believe there
are no limits to what we can achieve as we learn to know ourselves and each
other.
<br>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td></td><td align="center">
               <h3>Divine Sanction Structure</h3>
			  </td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;     The base of Divine Sanction will be its Citizens. For every five Citizens 
we will have a representative Legate, and for every five Legates we will 
have a Consul. At the top of this pyramid structure is the Imperatrix. The 
description of Legate and Consul can be found under the Senate of Divine Sanction 
  link. This structure is designed to ensure that all members have 
representation. As the guild grows and expands there will be more Legate and 
Consul positions available to those who demonstrate the desire and skills to 
fill the positions. Also as the guild grows the Legions will come into play. 
Legions will be based on Citizen levels and are there to provide a base for 
those of similar levels to meet, group and have appropriate events. There 
will also be a Centurion position created as the guild grows, this position 
will be that of an Junior Legate to ensure knowledge of guild policy in 
those new to leadership roles.
</td></tr>
<tr>
	<td></td><td>
	<br>
	<br>
	
<b>Terms:</b>
<br>
<br>

Citizen =Guild Member<br>
Centurion = Junior Officer<br>
Legate = Officer<br>
Consul =Senior Officer<br>
Imperatrix = Guild Leader<br>
Legion = Level Based Classification<br>

</td></tr></table>

	





                </td>
			  </tr>
			 </table>
		</td>
